---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import meganImage from "../../assets/images/megan.png";
---

<Layout title="About | Offbeat Canine - Dog Training and Education">
    <div class="container py-10">
        <article class="prose lg:prose-lg dark:prose-invert mx-auto">
            <div
                class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center gap-4 lg:-mx-10">
                <div>
                    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Meet Your Dog Trainer</h1>
                    <p class="font-display text-2xl">
                        Hi, I'm Megan Johnson, owner and trainer of Offbeat
                        Canine Training.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center justify-center md:justify-start">
                    <div
                        class="group max-w-96 overflow-hidden flex flex-col items-start bg-white p-4 pb-12 shadow-md rounded-sm border border-neutral-200 rotate-2 transform transition-transform ease-out duration-300 hover:-rotate-2 hover:shadow-lg">
                        <Image
                            src={meganImage}
                            alt="Photo of Megan and her two dogs"
                            class="my-0 sm:my-0 md:my-0 lg:my-0"
                        />
                        <div
                            class="absolute h-full top-0 left-1/2 w-12 transform origin-top-left bg-gradient-to-l from-white/20 to-transparent opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-hover:rotate-12 transition-all ease-out duration-300">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p>
                I provide private dog training, puppy training, behavior
                modification, reactivity training, recall training, and day
                training services throughout Southern New Hampshire. Based in
                Londonderry, NH, I work with dog owners who want practical
                results they can use in everyday life.
            </p>
            <p>
                Like many professional dog trainers, my story started with a
                love of dogs. Unlike many trainers, I didn't immediately jump
                into running a business. My experience comes from years spent
                working in dog daycare, dog walking, grooming, kennel
                management, rescue and rehabilitation, and hands-on animal care.
                Those experiences taught me that every dog is different, but
                more importantly, every owner is different too.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg lg:text-xl font-medium">
                That's why I don't believe in cookie-cutter training programs.
            </p>
            <p>
                Whether you're raising a new puppy, struggling with leash
                pulling, dealing with reactivity, or looking for better
                communication with your dog, my goal is to create a training
                plan that fits your lifestyle. Most of my clients aren't looking
                for a competition dog. They want a dog they can confidently walk
                through the neighborhood, bring to a brewery, enjoy on hiking
                trails, welcome guests around, or simply relax with at home.
            </p>
            <p>
                My training focuses on building engagement, communication,
                structure, and clear expectations between dogs and their owners.
                I believe training should be practical, realistic, and
                sustainable long after our lessons end.
            </p>
            <p>
                Since founding Offbeat Canine Training in 2024, I have worked
                with dogs of all breeds, ages, and temperaments throughout
                Southern New Hampshire. From puppy foundations and basic
                obedience to leash reactivity and advanced public access skills,
                I help owners build the knowledge and confidence needed to
                continue training on their own.
            </p>
            <p>
                In 2025, Offbeat Canine Training was voted Best Dog Trainer in
                New Hampshire through the Best of the 603 Awards. I am also an
                AKC Approved Evaluator for S.T.A.R. Puppy, Canine Good Citizen
                (CGC), Community Canine (CGCA), Urban CGC (CGCU), and Trick Dog
                titles.
            </p>
            <h2>Why Choose Offbeat Canine?</h2>
            <p>
                When you work with Offbeat Canine, you're not signing up for a
                one-size-fits-all program. You're working directly with a
                trainer who takes the time to understand your goals, your dog,
                and the challenges you're facing.
            </p>
            <p>Clients choose Offbeat Canine because they want:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Real-world dog training, not just obedience in a classroom
                </li>
                <li>
                    Private training tailored to their dog's individual needs
                </li>
                <li>Clear explanations and owner education</li>
                <li>Practical skills they can use at home and in public</li>
                <li>Ongoing support throughout their training journey</li>
                <li>
                    A trainer who values both the dog and the human end of the
                    leash
                </li>
            </ul>
            <h2>Serving Southern New Hampshire</h2>
            <p>
                Offbeat Canine Training proudly serves dog owners throughout
                Londonderry, Manchester, Derry, Windham, Salem, Hudson, Bedford,
                Merrimack, Nashua, Auburn, Chester, and surrounding Southern New
                Hampshire communities.
            </p>
            <p>
                If you're ready to build a better relationship with your dog,
                I'd love to help.
            </p>
            <p>
                Let's work together to help you and your dog learn to live in
                tune with each other.
            </p>
        </article>
    </div>
</Layout>
